# Root .env.example — shared infra coordinates ONLY.
#
# This file is owned by docker-compose.yml and the Makefile. Anything
# truly application-internal (worker counts, auth policy, OTel knobs,
# topic names) belongs in the per-service .env, e.g.
# apps/ledger-svc/.env.example.
#
# Discipline: each service owns its own internal/config package
# (Go's internal/ rule prevents sharing across apps). Today every
# service reads plain DATABASE_URL / REDIS_URL / KAFKA_BROKERS from
# this file. When a future service needs DIFFERENT infra coords —
# its own database, separate Kafka cluster, etc. — that service's
# config.go picks a service-prefixed name (LEDGER_DATABASE_URL,
# GATEWAY_DATABASE_URL, …) in its own struct tags, and we add the
# new name here. The shared default keeps working for services that
# don't need a split.
#
# Copy to .env (Makefile and docker-compose auto-load it).

# --- Postgres -----------------------------------------------------------------
# DATABASE_URL is consumed by both the binaries (via internal/config) and
# the migrate CLI. POSTGRES_* mirror the same values for the docker-compose
# postgres service's init env — keep them in sync if you change creds.
DATABASE_URL=postgres://phuong_dev:ledger_secret@localhost:5432/ledger_db?sslmode=disable
POSTGRES_USER=phuong_dev
POSTGRES_PASSWORD=ledger_secret
POSTGRES_DB=ledger_db

# --- Redis --------------------------------------------------------------------
REDIS_URL=redis://localhost:6379/0

# --- Kafka / Redpanda ---------------------------------------------------------
# Comma-separated for multi-broker; consumed by both confluent-kafka-go
# (joined back to a string) and rpk for topic admin.
KAFKA_BROKERS=localhost:9092
